messages.text: You don’t remember me, do you?
Cause I think I’d remember a killer redhead.
How about you and I get reacquainted?
This doesn’t have to be difficult, Kam.
Stay where you are and I’ll be right there
You’re a creepy unlisted number in a dark library
AKA, a super ideal place for murder.
You’re down on the fifth floor now.
And you just ran to the back stairwell
This can be so much easier...
Because you have something I want.
That tablet doesn’t belong to you.
Before I take it from you.
You’re on the wrong side of this
Dealing with things you don’t understand.
You’ve got a gun. I don’t.
Lucy, I’m in over my head
The armed redhead is after me
Sending all kinds of creeper texts.
YES, I have the stupid tablet.
Good. Because I’m freaking out right now!
How did she get my number?!?
Why is she gunning for you?
I mean, not to be rude
I just ran to my car.
Lucy, I’m here at the park.
At the edge of the woods
I told you I’d find you.
Once I get what I want.
Why don’t you just come out so we can finally talk in person?
How do you keep finding me?
You haven’t figured it out yet?
I hate this stupid thing so much.
Are you also some programming whiz?
But I have lost my iPhone before, which is close enough.
So how about you walk out from those trees with your hands in the air?
Kam walks out to see the red-headed woman with a gun.
There you are. Now do you recognize me?
Um, could you be more specific?
Remember from that BBQ last summer? We had a long conversation about potato salad?
You kept going on about mayo vs. mustard vs. vinegar based.
I mean, I do have many opinions about those things.  But I’m not good with names or faces.
Fine. You may better remember me as the Prof’s wife.
Oh SHOOT. It’s you! Why didn’t you say that earlier?
Because I’m an accomplished woman in my own right. And a man does not define me.
But now that you bring it up: Yeah, I’m his widow.
And I’m pretty pissed right now.
Shut up! I need answers. Now.
Then why are you after his stupid A.I. research?
Ok ok ok, so if could please put the gun down first, that would really help me think.
I don’t do well in these high-pressure situations
So I think there’s been a big misunderstanding.
And this is gonna sound really crazy but -.
So, the Prof was working on this self-driving car prototype.
But apparently the A.I. became sentient, and Stella went rogue and killed him.
You idiot!  There’s no such thing as a sentient A.I.!
But my friend Lucy is trapped inside Stella, and -
As in that lunatic girl from his class?
Why does everyone say she’s crazy? Am I missing something?
Lucy is a master at lying and manipulation
She’s an obsessed stalker who followed the Prof around.
Oh, she never mentioned that part.
Really? She never mentioned how she had an affair with my husband?
They were working together on the Stella project.
Spending a lot of time together.
I found out and so he broke it off.
I took him back and forgave him.
I wanted to move on because I still loved him. Flaws and all.
But Lucy wouldn’t stay away. She had this crazy vendetta.
So now I need you to give me that tablet so I can prove...
She wants the tablet so she can hide the evidence.
But I won’t let her get away with this.
No no no no. That’s impossible.
Lucy swore she didn’t do it.
Stella is the real killer. She needs the tablet to clear her name.
THERE’S NO SUCH THING AS SENTIENT A.I.
Give me the tablet, and I’ll prove it to you.
It’s coming closer. It’s a whizzing sound
No more BS.  Give me the tablet.  NOW.
Wait. I see headlights down the road. Is that -
But I must murder you now.
